### Create a menu with an invalid nested section (regression guard).
### Validates the TraverseAll adoption from commit 9b7a9e2:
### before the fix this would return HTTP 500 (InvalidOperationException) because nested
### .Match(v => v, e => throw ...) bubbled up past the Result track.
### After the fix it returns HTTP 422 with per-field violations for /name and /description
### (Section.Name is empty AND MenuItem.Description is empty).

@token = yourtoken
@hostId = 019E955C-89A3-7F92-A289-35F8823BC135

POST {{host}}/hosts/{{hostId}}/menus/create?api-version=2022-10-01
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Valid Menu",
    "description": "Valid Description",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "",
            "description": "Section description",
            "items": [
                { "name": "Item name", "description": "" }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

### Expected response shape:
### HTTP/1.1 422 Unprocessable Entity
### Content-Type: application/problem+json
### {
###   "type":"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4918#section-11.2",
###   "title":"One or more validation errors occurred.",
###   "status":422,
###   "errors":{
###     "name":["Name cannot be empty."],
###     "description":["Description cannot be empty."]
###   },
###   "code":"invalid-input",
###   "kind":"unprocessable-content"
### }
